"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678541","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-02","<p>My Department does not record the number of country parks that exist in each Parliamentary constituency. That is a matter for local authorities.</p><p>My Department asks councils to report on off-street parking including the charges they set. This would include charges set in country park car parks where they exist.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","61680","2017-02-02T13:52:38.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678541/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678541/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-25","Country Parks: Parking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many country parks managed by local authorities there are in each parliamentary constituency; and how many of those country parks charge for parking.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","61681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678542","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-01-31","<p>We have no plans to set out a time limit. Where a person becomes homeless intentionally, that condition may persist until the link between the deliberate act or omission that caused them to become intentionally homeless and the intentional homelessness itself has been broken. Whether that has happened will depend on the circumstances of the particular case and can be best judged by the local housing authority.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-01-31T13:53:47.153Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678542/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678542/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-25","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to establish a time-limit on the housing records of people made intentionally homeless.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","61689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678543","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-02","<p>Day centres and hostels will frequently operate as a care of address when required. For those people who are homeless and receive support under the main homelessness duty they are provided with temporary accommodation and can use that address.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-02T13:53:17.12Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678543/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678543/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-25","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to establish a postcode for people made homeless which may be used for job applications and registration with GPs.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","61690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678544","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-02","<p>My Department does not record the number of country parks that exist in each Parliamentary constituency. That is a matter for local authorities.</p><p>My Department asks councils to report on off-street parking including the charges they set. This would include charges set in country park car parks where they exist.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","61681","2017-02-02T13:52:38.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678544/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678544/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-25","Country Parks: Parking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of parking charges at country parks on visitor numbers.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","61680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678545","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-02","<p>The Home Building Fund is administered by the Homes and Communities Agency (HCA). Whilst the HCA does not ask specific questions with regard to business taxes, in line with UK government stated expectations, we require our customers to pay all relevant UK taxes.</p><p>The HCA’s commercial activities are subject to regulatory supervision as required by the Money Laundering Regulations 2007. Consequently, the HCA are registered with the financial services regulator, the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) for supervision of anti-money laundering controls. Tax evasion specifically is a criminal offence and now forms part of the definition of ‘criminal activity’ under the Fourth EU Money Laundering Directive.</p><p>The FCA and Anti Money Laundering laws and regulations require the HCA to adopt a risk-based Know Your Customer (KYC) programme, which requires the HCA to make additional enquiries with regard to tax status where our customer identification and verification checks identify possible red flags for tax avoidance/ evasion. For example, where a customer operates through a complex organisation structure, which may also be offshore based.</p><p>In these situations, the HCA will obtain independent tax advice (or other independent evidence) where we feel that this is necessary, the output of which may determine whether we can enter into or continue an existing relationship with a customer in the event of any concerns being identified.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-02T16:30:42.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678545/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678545/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-25","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if his Department will take steps to check whether recipients of loans from the Home Building Fund pay business taxes in the UK.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","61611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678546","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-02","<p>The Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport and I have extensively engaged with international broadcasters as we seek a new, positive and constructive partnership between Britain and the European Union. We are confident the UK film industry will continue to thrive.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-02T16:30:14.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678546/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678546/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-25","International Broadcasting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will make an assessment of the potential effects of the UK exiting the EU on the likelihood of international broadcasting companies continuing to base themselves in the UK.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","61686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678547","Department for Education","false","2017-02-07","<p>We are seeking to introduce a new statutory duty on the Secretary of State for Education through the Digital Economy Bill. This duty will ensure that in England when an adult aged 19 or over, who is considered to lack basic digital skills, studies for a relevant publicly-funded digital skills qualification, the individual will not be charged for that training. The costs will be met from the existing Adult Education Budget. The Adult Education Budget is £1.5bn in 2016-17, with indicative projections remaining at this level up to 2019-20.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2017-02-07T14:13:12.14Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678547/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678547/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678547/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-01-25","Digital Technology: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the cost of the amendments to the Digital Economy Bill on skills training on digital inclusion.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","61566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678548","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-31","<p>Government will respond to the recommendations of the National Infrastructure Commission's response through publication of the 5G Strategy. This strategy will outline the steps the Government is taking to ensure that the UK seizes the opportunity to be a world leader in 5G. Further updates on development of the strategy will issue around Budget 2017.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-31T16:45:18.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678548/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678548/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-25","5G: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to the National Infrastructure Commission's report, Connected future, published 15 December 2016, how standards for 5G coverage will be agreed.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","61565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678549","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-30","<p>All four mobile network operators have a legally binding licence obligation to provide voice and SMS text coverage to 90% of the UK landmass by the end of 2017. Ofcom is responsible to enforce these obligations and the Digital Economy Bill, will give Ofcom the power to issue large fines to any operator who fails to meet their licence obligations.</p><p> </p><p>Further details can be found in Ofcom's 2016 Connected Nations Report: https://www.ofcom.org.uk/research-and-data/infrastructure-research/connected-nations-2016.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-30T18:04:02.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678549/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678549/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-25","Mobile Phones: Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what her most recent estimate is of the percentage of geographic voice and data coverage provided by (a) O2, (b) EE, (c) Three and (d) Vodafone; and whether she expects those levels to reach 90 per cent geographic coverage for each of those operators by the end of 2017.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","61548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678550","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-30","<p>Yes.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-30T09:47:12.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678550/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678550/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-25","S4C Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether it will be a requirement of the independent review of S4C that the reviewer be proficient in the Welsh language.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","61761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678551","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>UK has not provided lethal supplies to opposition groups in Syria by any means.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-31T16:00:05.303Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678551/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678551/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-25","Syria: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether GPS guided parachutes have been used to facilitate arms drops to rebel forces in Syria in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","61768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678552","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>The UK Armed Forces do not have a GPS-guided parachute capability suitable to drop aid to besieged Syrian civilians. We continue to work with allies and partners on potential options for delivering aid, but the most effective means remains road deliveries of large quantities, organised by Humanitarian agencies and coordinated with authorities on the ground.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-31T15:59:17.167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678552/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678552/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-25","Syria: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department has received requests from other government departments for the use of GPS guided parachutes to drop aid to besieged Syrian civilians in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","61769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678554","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-30","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on Friday 27 January 2017 to Questions 61391, 61448, 61399, 61401, 61391 and 61405</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-01-30T17:10:03.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678554/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678554/answer","20170127_WQnA_extract_on_Trident_Missiles_Testing.docx","20170127_WQnA_extract_on_Trident_Missiles_Testing.docx","61391 - WQnA extract on Trident Missile Testing","61391 - WQnA extract on Trident Missile Testing","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678554/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-25","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK (a) armed forces personnel and (b) guests attending (i) Royal Navy SSGN and Trident II D5 Demonstrations and (ii) Shakedown Operations in (A) 2013 and (B) 2016 were accommodated in US hotels; and for how long such people were so accommodated.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","61542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678555","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>Our Trident missiles do not rely on US weather and navigational data. The UK's nuclear deterrent is completely operationally independent.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-01-31T16:01:37.88Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678555/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678555/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-25","Trident Missiles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether UK Trident missiles rely on (a) weather data and (b) navigational data provided by the US.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","61534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678556","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-30","<p>The Department has a 25 year support contract with Leonardo Helicopters to complete depth maintenance activity on Merlin helicopters at Royal Naval Air Service Culdrose. There are no plans to change this. I am looking forward to visiting the site this week.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-30T16:19:54.123Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678556/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678556/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-25","Helicopters: RNAS Culdrose","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has for the future of the depth servicing of helicopters at RNAS Culdrose.","false","Biography information for Derek Thomas","St Ives","Derek Thomas","61528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678557","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-30","<p>Under the Armed Forces Medical Deployability Standard (MDS) categories, Medically Fully Deployable (MFD) personnel are those who are medically fit for duty with no employment limitations.</p><p> </p><p>Medically Limited Deployable (MLD) personnel are those medically fit for duty with minor employment limitations. They may have a medical condition or functional limitation that prevents the meeting of all MFD requirements. Medically Not Deployable (MND) personnel are those medically fit for duty with major employment limitations. They are not fit to deploy on operations but may be deployable on UK based exercises.</p><p> </p><p>The following table shows the number of UK Regular Armed Forces personnel by MDS category in each year from 2010 to 2016, as at 1 April. Like for like data is not available before 2010.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>All</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>MFD</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>MLD</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>MND</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>MDS Not Known</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p><strong>1 April 2010</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All Services</p></td><td><p><strong> 177,897 </strong></p></td><td><p>143,253</p></td><td><p>18,101</p></td><td><p>13,615</p></td><td><p>2,928</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Naval Service</p></td><td><p><strong> 35,502 </strong></p></td><td><p>28,366</p></td><td><p>1,843</p></td><td><p>2,938</p></td><td><p>2,355</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Army</p></td><td><p><strong> 102,261 </strong></p></td><td><p>80,546</p></td><td><p>14,786</p></td><td><p>6,736</p></td><td><p>193</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p><strong> 40,134 </strong></p></td><td><p>34,341</p></td><td><p>1,472</p></td><td><p>3,941</p></td><td><p>380</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p><strong>1 April 2011</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All Services</p></td><td><p><strong> 176,816 </strong></p></td><td