"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678787","Department for International Trade","false","2017-01-30","<p>There have been 2,769 interactions with West Midlands businesses since July 2016. This includes a mixture of incoming enquiries and contact with existing clients.</p><p>Further data is not held centrally and it could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-01-30T17:56:21.77Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678787/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678787/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-01-25","Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many companies in the (a) West Midlands and (b) UK have made export enquiries to his Department since it was created; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","61661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678788","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-30","<p>We are doing all necessary preparatory work to make sure that we get the best deal for Britain, but as we have said before we will not provide a running commentary. <br><br></p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","61648","2017-01-30T18:34:47.237Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678788/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678788/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-25","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he has compiled a list of all UK rights and obligations arising from membership of EU agencies and institutions.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","61647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678789","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-30","<p>The Government has been consulting, and will continue to consult, with a broad range of stakeholders on the implications of our withdrawal from the European Union. The Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union has met with the TUC and Unison. <br><br></p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2017-01-30T17:13:20.613Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678789/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678789/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-25","Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 25 January 2017 to Question 60756, if he will provide a list of the trade unions referred to in that Answer.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","61663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678790","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-30","<p>We are doing all necessary preparatory work to make sure that we get the best deal for Britain, but as we have said before we will not provide a running commentary. <br><br></p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","61647","2017-01-30T18:34:47.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678790/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678790/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-25","UK Membership of EU: Treaties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he has compiled a list of all UK rights and obligations arising from third party agreements made by the EU to which the UK is a signatory.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","61648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678791","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-30","<p>The Supreme Court agreed with the Government's view that foreign affairs are a reserved matter. This Bill does not trigger the legislative consent process but we will continue to work closely with the Devolved Administrations.</p><p /> <p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2017-01-30T16:18:13.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678791/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678791/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-25","Legislative Consent Motions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps his Department took prior to the Supreme Court ruling of 24 January 2017 to prepare draft legislative consent motions for the devolved administrations on the Bill on the Government triggering Article 50.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","61559"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678792","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-30","<p>Ministers and officials across Government are engaging UK and EU business from every sector of the economy - this is a central element of our plan to get the right deal for Britain. We are listening and talking to a broad range of organisations, companies and institutions both in the UK, and abroad. Details of Ministerial meetings will be published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which will be made publicly available on GOV.UK.<strong><br></strong></p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2017-01-30T18:31:18.893Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678792/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678792/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-25","Business: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, on how many occasions he has met with businesses based in (a) Sheffield, (b) Leeds, (c) Manchester, (d) Newcastle, (e) Bradford, (f) Hull, (g) Liverpool and (h) Sunderland since 13 July 2016.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","61556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678793","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-02-02","<p>We are aiming to agree an ambitious and comprehensive trade deal with the EU.</p><p>We want to ensure that British companies have the maximum freedom to trade with and operate within European markets – and to let European businesses do the same in Britain.</p><p><strong><p><p></strong></p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-02-02T17:04:28.517Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678793/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678793/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-25","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if the Government will bring forward proposals during negotiations with the EU to allow specified industries to continue to access the single market on a sector-by-sector basis after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","61527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678794","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-30","<p>Stakeholder engagement is a central element of our plan to build a national consensus around our negotiating position; the whole of the government is listening and talking to as many organisations, companies and institutions as possible.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-30T17:39:07.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678794/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678794/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-25","European Banking Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions the Government has had with the European Banking Authority since the EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","61802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678829","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Government is not planning to make any response to the judgment, concerning Italian domestic law, by the Grand Chamber of the European Court of Human Rights. No assessment has been made of the implications of the case for United Kingdom surrogacy and family law.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-02-07T13:15:15.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678829/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678829/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-25","Surrogate Motherhood","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how they intend to respond to the ruling of the Grand Chamber of the European Court of Human Rights in the case <i>Paradiso and Campanelli v. Italy</i>; and what assessment they have made of the implications of the case for surrogacy and family law.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL4981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678830","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-06","<p>As my noble friend Baroness Goldie made clear in the House of Lords on 8 September 2016, &quot;the Government remains firmly committed to promoting and protecting the right to freedom of religion or belief, as set out in Article 18 of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights&quot;. We regularly raise our concerns about freedom of religion or belief with the government of Pakistan at a senior level. During his visit to Pakistan in November 2016, the Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson), discussed religious tolerance and the importance of safeguarding the rights of all Pakistan's citizens. The Parliamentary Under-Secretary for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my Hon. Friend the Member for Reading West (Mr Sharma), raised our concerns about religious minorities with Kamran Michael, Pakistani Minister for Human Rights, and Barrister Zafarullah Khan, the Prime Minister's Special Assistant for Human Rights during his visit to Pakistan in January 2017. The Government continues to urge Pakistan to honour in practice all its human rights obligations, including its commitment to Article 18 of the UN Universal Declaration of Human Rights, and to uphold the rule of law.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2017-02-06T17:54:03.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678830/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678830/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-25","Pakistan: Religious Freedom","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the forthcoming periodic review of human rights in Pakistan, whether they intend to ask the government of Pakistan to affirm its commitment to Article 18 of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights, including the freedom to change one’s belief or not have any kind of religious belief.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL4982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678831","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-01-31","<p>The National Institute of Economic and Social Research (NISER) resolved the errors made in the original report without drawing any further funding from DCLG. The costs to DCLG in identifying the errors and ensuring that NIESR rectified them were met through existing departmental resource. The peer review of this work was done on a pro bono basis by members of the existing Troubled Families independent advisory group comprising independent academics and analysts from other Government Departments. No reduction was made to the fee paid to NIESR.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2017-01-31T15:54:49.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678831/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678831/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-25","Families: Disadvantaged","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth on 25 January (HL4381), what was the cost of resolving the errors in the original report; how that cost was met; and what reduction, if any, was made in the fee payable to National Institute of Economic and Social Research.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL4983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678832","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-02","<p>The NCS Trust is being incorporated as a Royal Charter body. The Charter specifies that the Trust must have regard to 'encouraging participants to take an interest in debate on matters of local or national political interest, and promoting their understanding of how to participate in national and local elections.'</p><p> </p><p>NCS is not primarily a citizenship education programme; it is about broader personal development and social mixing. Nonetheless government wants NCS to provide young people with the opportunity to develop a range of skills, including political literacy.</p><p> </p><p>Later this year, Government plans to publish guidance on NCS for schools and colleges, which will include a link to citizenship education.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2017-02-02T13:09:40.153Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678832/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678832/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-25","Voluntary Work: Young People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to ensure that National Citizen Service participants experience citizenship education and political literacy as part of any programmes they undertake.","false","Biography information for Lord Bird",,"Lord Bird","HL4984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678833","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-02","<p>Government is supporting social action to grow and become part of the normal routine in public services and communities. Through the Centre for Social Action, Government has invested over £40m in helping grow 215 impactful programmes involving over 2 million volunteers across the country.</p><p> </p><p>Government continues to support Step Up to Serve’s #iwill campaign which aims to increase the opportunities for 10-20 year olds to take part in meaningful youth lead social action by 2020.</p><p> </p><p>The recently launched £40 million #iwill Fund jointly funded by government and Big Lottery Fund will help to increase the number of opportunities available to young people.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2017-02-02T13:14:50.273Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678833/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678833/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-25","Voluntary Work","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to help social action projects overcome their hidden costs; and what steps they are taking to ensure that social action projects are youth-led.","false","Biography information for Lord Bird",,"Lord Bird","HL4985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678834","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-07","<p>These questions are a matter for the Irish Government.</p><p>However, it is my understanding that: the Irish Human Rights and Equality Commission, like the Northern Ireland Human Rights Commission, is a UN ‘A status’ accredited National Human Rights Institution, structured and operated in accordance with the Paris Principles; that the Republic of Ireland ratified the Council of Europe Framework Convention on National Minorities in 1999; that the Republic of Ireland gave further effect to provisions of the Convention for the Protection of Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms in domestic legislation through the European Convention of Human Rights Act 2003, and that since 1998 a number of pieces of legislation have been introduced in the Republic of Ireland including the Employment Equality Acts 1998 and 2004.</p><p>The UK Government remains committed to reforming our domestic human rights framework. We will consider further the Bill of Rights once we know the arrangements for our EU exit and consult fully on our proposals in the full knowledge of the new constitutional landscape that will create. The UK has a proud tradition of respect for human rights which long pre-dates the Human Rights Act 1998.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Dunlop","HL4987 ; HL4988 ; HL4989 ; HL4990","2017-02-07T12:51:55.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678834/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678834/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-01-25","Human Rights: Republic of Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Republic of Ireland has established a Human Rights Commission with a mandate and remit equivalent to that within Northern Ireland as provided for by paragraph 9 of the chapter on rights, safeguards and equality of opportunity in the Belfast Agreement 1998.","false","Biography information for Lord Kilclooney",,"Lord Kilclooney","HL4986"
