"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677979","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-27","<p>The strength of the Royal Marine Reserves by stationed locations in London, Bristol, Liverpool and Glasgow as of 1 October 2016 is provided in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Royal Marine Reserves</p></td><td><p>888</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>236</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>City of Bristol</p></td><td><p>195</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Liverpool</p></td><td><p>213</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Glasgow City</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Defence Statistic (Tri Service)</p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><ol><li>Royal Marine Reserve includes High Readiness Reserves, those volunteer reserves serving on Full Time Reserve Service and Additional Duties Commitments.</li><li>Military personnel numbers are sourced from the Joint Personnel Administration (JPA) system. Location data are based on the stationed location of the individual as recorded in the ‘Assignment Location’ field of the JPA system. The figures are based on Service personnel’s stationed location and not their location of residence – where personnel work is not necessarily where they live. For Reservists with specialist skills posted to National Units, the Posted Unit may be a long way from where they live. Personnel deployed on operations to an area away from their stationed location are shown against their most recent stationed location.</li></ol><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-01-27T14:06:04.447Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677979/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677979/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Marines: Reserve Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the strength is of the Royal Marine Reserves in (a) London, (b) Bristol, (c) Liverpool and (d) Glasgow.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","61313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677980","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-27","<p>The trained and untrained strength of the Royal Marines Band Service is published in the Royal Navy and Royal Marines Monthly Personnel Situation Report. The figures as at 1 December 2016 are shown as:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Trained</p></td><td><p>350</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Untrained</p></td><td><p>70</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>420</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Notes:</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>1. Regular Marines in the Royal Marines Band Service.</p><p> </p><p>2. Totals are rounded separately so may not equal the sum of their rounded parts.</p><p> </p><p>The link to the Royal Navy and Royal Marines Monthly Personnel Situation Report published on 19 January 2017 giving further details can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/584247/20170116_-_FINAL_-_RN_RM_Monthly_Situation_Report__rounded___2_.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/584247/20170116_-_FINAL_-_RN_RM_Monthly_Situation_Report__rounded___2_.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-27T13:58:28.933Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677980/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677980/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Marines: Military Bands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) trained and (b) untrained strength is of the Royal Marine Band Service.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","61314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677981","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-01","<p>A planned amendment to the existing Babcock Defence Support Group contract to provide equipment support at the Defence School of Transport is in the process of being finalised.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-02-01T16:30:28.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677981/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677981/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Defence School of Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost and length is of Babock International's contract to run the Defence School of Transport, Leconfield; and what that company's plans are for the running of the Defence School of Transport.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","61408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677982","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>The intent to outsource the Equipment Support activity at the Defence School of Transport does not include the sale or transfer of Ministry of Defence real estate to Babcock. Babcock will operate from the existing workshop facility granted to them under licence for the duration of the contract.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-31T17:08:28.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677982/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677982/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Defence School of Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether Babock International's contract to run the Defence School of Transport, Leconfield has led to the permanent sale of his Department's land to that company.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","61409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677983","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>The Ministry of Defence (in conjunction with the Department for Transport) conducts a programme of routinely surveying the Country's strategic waterways to ensure both port security and safety from ordnance.</p><p>There are well established maritime procedures to ensure any hazards and associated activities are promulgated to shipping and, where necessary, exclusion zones established and enforced. This ensures that when ordnance is occasionally discovered under water or below the high water mark, it remains undisturbed until rendered safe by a Royal Navy Explosive Ordnance Disposal Unit.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-31T16:02:30.04Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677983/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677983/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Seas and Oceans: Bomb Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps the Government is taking to ensure UK waters are clear of unexploded ordnance.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","61430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677984","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-27","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not provide the single Services with central guidance on this matter. Mess establishments have charitable status and are responsible for setting their own membership criteria.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-01-27T13:57:34.32Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677984/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677984/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what instructions his Department issues to the armed services limiting the entry to mess establishments of retired members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","61426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677985","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>In respect of UK land Explosive Ordnance Disposal (EOD) operations, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) has a very close relationship with industry when discussing Countering Explosive Ordnance. Within the last 18 months, the MOD has worked closely with industry to help create 'Counter-Improvised Explosive Device (C-IED) UK', a body that represents the whole of UK C-IED industry. The MOD sits on the Executive Committee of that body and ensures that industry understands UK MOD requirements in significant detail.</p><p>At present the MOD does not have a requirement to outsource UK maritime EOD tasks to commercial companies, therefore no approach has been made to industry.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-31T16:18:10.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677985/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677985/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677985/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Bomb Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions the Government has had with industry experts on identifying and dealing with unexploded ordnance.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","61432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677986","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-27","<p>No UK Government Ministers attended the Demonstration and Shakedown Operations (DASO) in the US in 2012 and 2016. Overall, 30 UK personnel attended the 2012 DASO and 42 attended in 2016. All attendees required accommodation in US hotels for periods of between two and four nights depending on whether they were witnessing rehearsal activity and the launch or only the launch.</p><p> </p><p>In 2012, eight guests were invited on board the HMS Vigilant; three military and five civilians. Three of these guests were considered VIPs. In 2016, seven guests were invited on board HMS Vengeance; four military and three civilians. Three of these guests were considered VIPs.</p><p> </p><p>In 2012, eleven civilian guests, including UK Government officials, industrial partners and academics, attended the DASO on board the Launch Area Surface Ship, and 28 civilians attended the DASO in 2016.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","61392 ; 61399 ; 61401 ; 61405 ; 61448","2017-01-27T14:48:25.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677986/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677986/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677986/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Government Ministers attended Royal Navy SSBN and Trident II D5 demonstration and shakedown operations in (a) 2012 and (b) 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","61391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677987","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-27","<p>No UK Government Ministers attended the Demonstration and Shakedown Operations (DASO) in the US in 2012 and 2016. Overall, 30 UK personnel attended the 2012 DASO and 42 attended in 2016. All attendees required accommodation in US hotels for periods of between two and four nights depending on whether they were witnessing rehearsal activity and the launch or only the launch.</p><p> </p><p>In 2012, eight guests were invited on board the HMS Vigilant; three military and five civilians. Three of these guests were considered VIPs. In 2016, seven guests were invited on board HMS Vengeance; four military and three civilians. Three of these guests were considered VIPs.</p><p> </p><p>In 2012, eleven civilian guests, including UK Government officials, industrial partners and academics, attended the DASO on board the Launch Area Surface Ship, and 28 civilians attended the DASO in 2016.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","61391 ; 61399 ; 61401 ; 61405 ; 61448","2017-01-27T14:48:25.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677987/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677987/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677987/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK national civilian guests were aboard the US Naval Ship Waters T-AGS-45 during Royal Navy SSBN and Trident II D5 demonstration and shakedown operations in 2012.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","61392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677988","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>Vanguard ballistic missile submarine Demonstration and Shakedown Operations (DASO) are conducted in conjunction with the US Department of Defense. All 11 DASOs resulted in the submarine successfully being certified to return to the operational cycle.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-01-31T16:06:31.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677988/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677988/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677988/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether officials at his Department alerted officials in the US Department about the misfired Trident missile, during tests off the Eastern US coast in June 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","61370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677989","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>In 2012, ten guests attended the Demonstration and Shakedown Operations (DASO) Trafalgar dinner function, six military personnel and four civilians. This included one civilian VIP. There was no DASO Trafalgar dinner in June 2016.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","61400 ; 61404","2017-01-31T16:08:09.03Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677989/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677989/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-24","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many civilian guests who were invited by commanding officers attended the Trafalgar Dinner Function during Royal Navy SSBN and Trident II D5 demonstration and shakedown operations in (a) 2012 and (b) 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","61403"
