"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678035","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-01","<p>We have not yet held discussions with Scott Pruitt on international cooperation on climate change. When we do, we will be clear about our views on the issue.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-02-01T14:13:40Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678035/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678035/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678035/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-24","USA: Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had on international cooperation on climate change with Scott Pruitt, President Trump's nominee for Administrator of the US Environmental Protection Agency.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","61333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678036","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-01","<p>We have not yet held discussions with Rex Tillerson on international cooperation on climate change. When we do, we will be clear about our views on the issue.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-02-01T14:16:32.827Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678036/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678036/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678036/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-24","USA: Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had on international cooperation on climate change with Rex Tillerson, President Trump's nominee for Secretary of State.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","61335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678037","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-01","<p>The UK remains concerned about cases of Ali Mohammed al-Nimr, Dawood al-Marhoon and Abdullah al-Zaher. Our Embassy in Riyadh last raised the three men's cases on 19 January 2017 and our expectation remains that they will not be executed. We will continue to closely follow their cases.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-01T13:13:07.633Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678037/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678037/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678037/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-24","Saudi Arabia: Capital Punishment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2016 to Question 45557, what recent representations he has made to his Saudi Arabian counterpart on the cases of Ali Mohammed al-Nimr, Abdullah al-Zaher and Dawood al-Marhoon.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","61453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678038","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-01","<p>On 24 and 25 January I issued statements regarding the latest settlement announcements. I raised the issue of settlements with the Israeli Deputy Foreign Minister when we spoke on 10 January 2017.</p><p>The UK's position on settlements is clear. They are illegal under international law, present an obstacle to peace, and take us further away from a two-state solution. We regularly raise our concerns on this issue with the Government of Israel and urge it to reverse its systematic policy of settlement expansion. We believe the construction of settlements in the Occupied Palestinian Territories is illegal, which is why we supported UN Security Council Resolution 2334 (2016).</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-01T13:15:53.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678038/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678038/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678038/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-24","Israeli Settlements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Israeli counterpart on the building of Israeli settlements on Palestinian land; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","61470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678039","Department for International Development","false","2017-01-31","<p>The UK remains closely engaged with the United Nations which is establishing a returns working group to support coordinated, safe returns in Mosul.</p><p>DFID officials regularly meet with donor colleagues, including the US and Germany, in Baghdad, Erbil, and other donor forums to discuss issues including safe returns. DFID officials also raised the issue of safe returns with the Kurdistan Regional Government who gave assurances that returns will be voluntary and dignified. The Minister of State discussed stabilisation with Iraqi and US officials during his visit in November 2016.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-01-31T17:36:32.517Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678039/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678039/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678039/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-01-24","Iraq: Internally Displaced People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that internally displaced persons in Iraq who have fled from Mosul are not forcibly returned to Mosul following the recapture of that city; and when she last discussed that matter with her counterparts in (a) the US and (b) Germany.","false","Biography information for Mr Pat McFadden","Wolverhampton South East","Mr Pat McFadden","61455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678040","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-01","<p>The UK is helping the Government of Iraq to stabilise areas liberated from Daesh. We have provided £8.25 million for UN-led efforts to manage explosive hazards, including a £3.5m contribution to support work in and around Mosul. We are also providing technical advice and support from the British Defence Attaché in Baghdad, and the British Army's Senior Explosive Ordnance Disposal and Search Expert. In total, the international community has contributed £88.25 million for the management of explosive hazards, primarily through the UN Mine Action Service.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-01T14:25:58.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678040/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678040/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678040/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-24","Iraq: Bomb Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much funding has been allocated to de-mining in and surrounding Mosul since the offensive against Daesh.","false","Biography information for Mr Pat McFadden","Wolverhampton South East","Mr Pat McFadden","61454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678041","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-01","<p>We are working with the Government of Iraq and our Coalition partners to stabilise areas in and surrounding Mosul that have been liberated from Daesh, including through the provision of targeted support and technical advice through the UN Mine Action Service (UNMAS). We have provided £8.25 million for UNMAS-led efforts to manage explosive hazards, to help to provide a safe environment for displaced Iraqis to return home. The UK is also the Global Coalition military Counter-Improvised Explosive Device training lead in Iraq.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-01T14:28:02.517Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678041/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678041/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678041/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-24","Iraq: Bomb Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to implement an international strategy for the removal of mines, improvised explosive devices and other explosive devices in and surrounding Mosul since the offensive against Daesh.","false","Biography information for Mr Pat McFadden","Wolverhampton South East","Mr Pat McFadden","61457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678042","Department of Health","false","2017-02-01","<p>The Department and the National Health Service takes protection of data very seriously. The Government will respond shortly to the recent consultation on The National Data Guardian for Health and Care Review of Data Security, Consents and Opt-Outs, published 6 July 2016.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not comment on security matters.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","61473","2017-02-01T13:31:29.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678042/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678042/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678042/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-24","NHS: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will estimate the cost to the NHS of cyber attacks in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","61503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678043","Department of Health","false","2017-02-01","<p>NHS Choices provides advice for new mothers on keeping fit and healthy with a baby, including exercise, healthy eating and weight loss. Details of that advice can be found here:</p><p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/pregnancy-and-baby/pages/keeping-fit-and-healthy.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/pregnancy-and-baby/pages/keeping-fit-and-healthy.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p>Advice from NHS Choices is also made available to expectant and new parents through Start4Life.</p><p> </p><p>The NHS Choices website has general information on weight loss including a free NHS Weight Loss guide, and extensive information on preventing heart disease including a section on ‘How to look after your heart’ available here:</p><p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Livewell/Healthyhearts/Pages/Lifestylechanges.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.nhs.uk/Livewell/Healthyhearts/Pages/Lifestylechanges.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p>NHS Choices also includes detailed advice on congenital heart disease during pregnancy and what the mother-to-be should do to safeguard her own health and that of her child available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/pregnancy-and-baby/pages/congenital-heart-disease-pregnant.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/pregnancy-and-baby/pages/congenital-heart-disease-pregnant.aspx</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","61507","2017-02-01T10:44:41.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678043/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678043/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678043/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-24","Pregnancy: Diets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the NHS provides advice to pregnant women on weight loss after birth.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","61506"
