"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678113","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-27","<p>Ensuring that offenders have access to suitable and stable accommodation is integral to breaking the cycle of reoffending.</p><p>As part of our probation reforms all offenders, including those sentenced to less than 12 months, now receive targeted support when they leave prison to help them reintegrate into society. This includes help to find accommodation. We are currently conducting a comprehensive review of the probation system, which will look at how we can improve outcomes for offenders. The review will be completed in April this year.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-01-27T14:36:56.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678113/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678113/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678113/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-01-24","Prisoners' Release: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps her Department is taking to help ex-offenders find accommodation on their release from prison.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","61499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678114","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-27","<p>The figures for the total costs associated with the case will be published in due course.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","61496","2017-01-27T11:53:06.053Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678114/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678114/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678114/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-24","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of pursuing the appeal to the Supreme Court in the case of R Miller and Dos Santos v the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","61497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678115","Prime Minister","false","2017-01-31","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Statement made by the Secretary of State for Defence, my right hon. Friend the Member for Sevenoaks (Mr Fallon) on 23 January 2017, Official Report, columns 23-42.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-01-31T16:51:03.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678115/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678115/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678115/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-01-24","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, when she was made aware of the results of the tests of the UK's nuclear deterrent in June 2016; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","61465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678116","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-27","<p>I have regular discussions with the Prime Minster and my Cabinet colleagues on a wide range of issues.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-01-27T12:18:42.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678116/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678116/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678116/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-01-24","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions his Department has had with the (a) Prime Minister and (b) Ministry of Defence on tests on the UK nuclear deterrent in June 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","61501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678117","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-27","<p>Section 2 of the Scotland Act 2016 delivers the cross-party Smith Commission Agreement by placing the Sewel Convention on a statutory footing.</p><p>The UK Government’s position on the Sewel Convention has not changed since the passage of the Scotland Act 2016.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-01-27T12:20:10.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678117/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678117/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678117/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-01-24","Scotland Act 2016","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, with reference to comments in the Supreme Court's ruling in R (on the application of Miller and another) v Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union on the purpose of the legislative recognition of the Sewel Convention in the Scotland Act 2016 being to entrench it as a convention, if his Department will examine the purpose, validity and legal effectiveness of section 2 of the Scotland Act 2016.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","61526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678118","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-31","<p>The Emergency Towing Vessel, IEVOLI BLACK, will operate in designated UK waters and must comply with the relevant UK maritime safety regulations.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-31T12:16:29.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678118/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678118/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678118/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-24","MV Ievoli Black","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether it is the Government's policy that the UK maritime safety regulations are applicable to the operation and crewing of the emergency towing vessel Ievoli Black.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","61471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678119","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-27","<p>The Maritime and Coastguard Agency is not required to produce a regulatory impact assessment as the requirement for an Emergency Towing Vessel is not mandated by UK regulation.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-27T12:21:39.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678119/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678119/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678119/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-24","Tugboats: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has instructed the Maritime and Coastguard Agency to conduct a regulatory impact assessment on chartering a foreign-registered emergency towing vessel; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","61472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678120","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-31","<p>The First Road Investment Strategy (2015-2020) committed £7.7Bn to capital improvement across England’s motorway and Major trunk roads, most of which will reduce congestion. Similarly, the Government is already allocating £6Bn to councils inn England up to 2021 to help improve the local road network.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, new funding of £1.3Bn was announced in the Autumn Statement to help support infrastructure projects; £1.1Bn for local roads and £220M to relieve congestion on Strategic routes. Congestion on roads outside of England is a matter for the respective devolved administrations.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-31T13:14:44.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678120/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678120/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-24","Road Traffic Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent steps his Department has taken to reduce road congestion.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","61341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678121","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-27","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) is working with Vauxhall and other manufacturers and distributors to ensure that they meet their vehicle safety obligations as set out in the Code of Practice on Vehicle Safety Defects, the General Product Safety Regulations and associated legislation.</p><p> </p><p>It is the responsibility of manufacturers and distributors, including Vauxhall, to ensure that all vehicles placed on the market are safe. This includes second-hand vehicles subject to a safety recall. The DVSA and I have discussed this issue with Vauxhall.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-27T12:29:17.827Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678121/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678121/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-24","Vauxhall Motors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with (a) Vauxhall and (b) auto trade representatives on whether used Vauxhall Zafira B models, subject to recall by Vauxhall for safety reasons, are on sale.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","61359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678122","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-31","<p>Highways England’s monitoring of the first two ‘all lane running’ smart motorways - on the M25 between junctions 5 to 7 and 23 to 27 - over their first 12 months of operation has shown that traffic flows have increased, users at peak periods are on average saving time and that journey time reliability has improved.</p><p> </p><p>Highways England is closely monitoring the performance of all subsequent smart motorway schemes that have opened, most recently on the M1 and M6, and their initial data is encouraging. All major road schemes are routinely monitored as part of the Post Opening Project Evaluation programme and this is regularly published on Highways England’s website.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-31T12:19:58.157Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678122/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678122/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678122/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-24","Motorways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of average journey times on smart motorways compared with the same journey prior to the introduction of smart motorway technology.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","61368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678123","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-27","<p>Latest ONS data, taken from the Annual Survey of Hours and Earnings (ASHE) relating to April 2015, shows the proportion of employees in work contributing to an occupational defined benefit scheme was reported to be 28.3%, largely unchanged since 2012. The proportion of employees in work contributing to either an occupational defined contribution, Group Personal or Group Stakeholder pension scheme was reported to be 34.3%, almost double the 17.2% reported in 2012.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-01-27T11:04:07.153Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678123/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678123/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678123/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the proportion of people in work who have a defined (a) benefit and (b) contribution pension scheme.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","61389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678124","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-30","<p>DWP does not hold the information requested as the Master Trust Assurance Framework is voluntary and overseen by the Institute of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales. The data which most closely matches that requested can be found on the Pension Regulator’s website, at the following address:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.thepensionsregulator.gov.uk/doc-library/dc-trust-presentation-of-scheme-return-data-2017.aspx%20" target="_blank">http://www.thepensionsregulator.gov.uk/doc-library/dc-trust-presentation-of-scheme-return-data-2017.aspx</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Pension Regulator publishes annual statistics on occupational defined contribution trust-based pension schemes and memberships. The latest data shows that on 31<sup>st</sup> December 2016, 13 Master Trusts were on the published list of schemes that have achieved Master Trust assurance. This figure does not include any Master Trusts that may have achieved Master Trust assurance but do not appear on the list, for example because they have chosen not to or are in the process of applying.</p><p> </p><p>As mentioned above, the Master Trust Assurance Framework accreditation process is voluntary. A scheme wishing to undertake this accreditation will engage a Reporting Accountant to carry out the work. There are no requirements for schemes to inform the Regulator that they are undertaking an assurance exercise or to provide the report, unless they wish to apply to join the Regulator’s published list.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-01-30T17:22:27.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678124/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678124/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678124/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many Master Trust products have been independently reviewed against the Master Trust Assurance framework.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","61386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678125","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-30","<p>Pension Credit is an income-related, non-taxable benefit which is intended to provide people of pension age with financial assistance to enable a minimum guaranteed amount to meet living costs in Great Britain. It is a basic condition of entitlement that a person be in Great Britain to receive it. Although Pension Credit is not intended to subsidise absences from Great Britain, in certain circumstances entitlement to the benefit can continue during a temporary absence abroad.</p><p> </p><p>It is the Government’s view that the current rule, which allows entitlement to continue for up to four consecutive weeks during a period of absence from Great Britain, is reasonable and justified. It allows time, for example, for holidays and visiting families, without a person having to reclaim Pension Credit on their return to Great Britain. There are exceptions to the general four week rule. Pension Credit can continue for up to 26 weeks where medical treatment or medically approved convalescence is required outside Great Britain. Where the absence is in connection with a death of a partner or close relative then entitlement can continue for up to eight weeks.</p><p> </p><p>This approach aligns Pension Credit and Housing Benefit with Universal Credit and provides consistency across these benefits and we have no plans to change this.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-01-30T17:15:21.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678125/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678125/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678125/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Pension Credit: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will take steps to allow people temporarily living abroad to claim pension credit for longer.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","61407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678126","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-02-01","<p>The impact of this policy was outlined in the Summer Budget policy costings document published in July 2015. All costings in that document were subject to scrutiny by the Office for Budget Responsibility.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-02-01T15:30:50.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678126/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678126/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678126/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 24 January 2017 to Question 60655, on universal credit and housing benefit, if he will place in the Library the assumptions and modelling on which those estimates are based.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","61417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678127","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-31","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 12 December 2016 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=56552" target="_blank">UIN56552</a>.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-31T12:18:27.883Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678127/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678127/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678127/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Motability: Inverclyde","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Inverclyde constituency had a motability car in (a) 2014, (b) 2015 and (c) 2016.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","61306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678128","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-31","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-31T12:14:19.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678128/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678128/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678128/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Motability: Inverclyde","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Inverclyde constituency had their motability car removed after changes to their benefit entitlement in (a) 2014, (b) 2015 and (c) 2016.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","61307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678129","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-27","<p>The Universal Credit service monitors the level of telephone calls every day to ensure appropriate levels of resource are in place, and has the flexibility to deploy additional people at short notice if needed. There are also plans in place to increase resource to meet the rise in demand as Universal Credit roles out.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-01-27T12:51:14.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678129/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678129/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678129/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will increase the number of call operators employed to process universal credit claims.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","61326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678130","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-27","<p>Of the 290,000 people on Universal Credit, as at June 2016, 310 (0.1%) had received Severe Disablement Allowance at some point between August 1999 and May 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-27T14:19:42.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678130/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678130/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678130/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many universal credit claimants previously received severe disability allowance.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","61327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678131","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-27","<p>The relationship between Universal Credit and local authority debt is complex, with many different factors at play. We continue to work closely with landlords, Local Authorities, housing associations and other organisations in order to understand the issues involved and address any concerns regarding the effects of Universal Credit.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-01-27T11:31:49.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678131/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678131/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678131/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-24","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the effectiveness of recent changes to housing payments and universal credits on local government debt.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","61328"
